{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"aed8b63927090d2d9","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"You are a web research agent. Use WebSearch and WebFetch (load them via ToolSearch query \"select:WebSearch,WebFetch\" first if not available). The current date is June 2026.\n\nRESEARCH ANGLE: Feasibility of on-device training/fine-tuning of an ~8B model on a 16 GB Apple-silicon Mac, plus self-training / RLVR for small models.\n\nResearch concretely:\n- LoRA / QLoRA fine-tuning of 7-8B models with Apple MLX (mlx-lm lora) on Apple silicon: memory requirements, can it fit in 16 GB unified memory, training time, quality. Look for mlx-examples / mlx-lm LoRA docs and benchmarks, blog posts of people doing LoRA on M-series Macs with 16GB or noting 16GB is tight.\n- Quantified: how much RAM does QLoRA on 8B need; is 16 GB enough (often quoted: needs careful config, batch size 1, quantized base).\n- RLVR (Reinforcement Learning from Verifiable Rewards) on small models: does it work for coding/math (e.g. results on 7B models, DeepSeek-R1-distill, TinyZero, \"RL on 1.5B/3B/7B\"). What's needed (verifiable reward = tests pass).\n- Self-rewarding / self-training / self-distillation for small models improving their own coding: does it actually lift capability, or plateau/collapse.\n- Distillation from a stronger teacher into a small student for coding: effectiveness (e.g. DeepSeek-R1 distilled models, Qwen distillation).\n\nRun at least 4-5 searches. Fetch authoritative sources (Apple MLX GitHub/docs, arXiv, HF blog, TinyZero/Jiayi Pan, technical blogs). Cross-check numbers.\n\nReturn a list of FALSIFIABLE CLAIMS each with: claim, number/detail, source URL. Flag conflicts. Do NOT write files. Return findings only as your final message."},"uuid":"67d8e083-b3c1-4543-9951-cce155cfa6c1","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:37.873Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec